cular on English, as they cross geographical and social spaces. By showing how the transnational mobility of labor is dependent on the selection and performance of particular assemblages of linguistic resources that index migrants as labor and not as people, the book provides a powerful lens with which to examine how migration contributes to relationships of inequality and how such inequalities are produced and challenged on the terrain of language.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexSocial aspectszSingapore. 0aForeign workers, FilipinozSingapore. 0aLanguage and languagesxEconomic aspectszPhilippines. 0aWomen foreign workerszSingaporexLanguage. 0aWomen household employeeszSingapore. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aEnglish.  aLanguage.  adomestic work.  alabour migration.  amigration.  amultilingualism.  atransnationalism.1 aKubota, Ryuko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorgan, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPennycook, Alastair, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066312908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309900940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783099009423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783099009/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066312-9  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPAL